1. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper deals with finding maximum independent sets in graphs, which is a classic problem in algorithms and data structures. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes a technique to improve the performance of local search algorithms, which is a common technique used in AI for solving optimization problems. 
3. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - The paper discusses the use of cutting high-degree vertices to improve local search performance, which is similar to the idea of pruning in evolutionary algorithms. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper mentions the use of the proposed technique on huge complex networks, which is a common topic in social and information networks research. 
5. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The paper deals with combinatorial optimization, which is a topic in discrete mathematics.
